Chart K: Develop four questions or ideas about climate change from your visualizations.

1. Long-Term Warming Trends in Specific Cities:

Are certain cities experiencing more pronounced warming trends than others, and which historical periods show the most significant temperature increases?

2. Shifts in Temperature Distribution Over Time:

Has the temperature distribution widened over decades, suggesting more extreme heat events or an upward shift in baseline temperatures?

3. Seasonal Patterns and Changing Extremes:

Are the differences between summer and winter temperatures changing, and are certain months warming at a faster rate than others, indicating a potential shift in seasonal cycles?

4. Regional/Latitudinal Contrasts:

Do lower-latitude (tropical) regions already experiencing higher baseline temperatures face a disproportionate temperature increase over time, or are mid-latitude regions catching up due to accelerated warming trends?

Dataset name: Climate Change: Earth Surface Temperature Data

Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/berkeleyearth/climate-change-earth-surface-temperature-data
